title: For Sale:  S&W K-22 Revolver with Leupold Scope
postcontent:
I'm selling my very special Smith & Wesson K-22 revolver, Model 17-4.  This is a beautiful early .22 revolver, the serial number indicates it was made in 1957.  It has some marks on the barrel, but no rust or corrosion, just signs of good, honest wear.  Mechanically it's in perfect condition, locking up tight like a Smith should, with an amazing crisp trigger that's perfect for hunting or target work.  These are beautiful guns that function well above expectations.

This K-22 is fitted with a Leupold 2-power pistol scope, M8-2X.  The scope was sent to the Leupold factory for inspection and reconditioning in 2004.  I have the paperwork to verify this.  The scope is mounted to the pistol with a sturdy B-Square mount, especially made for S&W pistols.  It replaces the rear sight and clamps on the barrel in the front.  The original factory K-22 sight will be included.  As shaky as I am, I have experienced dime-size groups at 25 yards.  The gun has not been fired in years, but it's ready to go for small game or the target range.

The original factory wooden grips were replaced with oversize Pachmayr rubber grips which give better control for shooting.  The original grips will be included with the package.  The gun comes in a sturdy, lockable, carrying case, with the original grips and sights, and a complementary box of ammo.

You just can't get them like this anymore.  This pistol is very tight and a real nice shooter, and very collectable.  What a perfect gift it would make for someone special.  I'm asking $550 for this fine .22 revolver and scope package.  Contact me immediately so we can talk about this, and make an appointment for viewing.

title: For Sale:  East German Makarov, 9X18
postcontent:
I'm selling my beautiful East German Makarov pistol.  The finish is excellent, only very minor holster wear.  The East Germans are considered to be the finest manufactured Makarovs on the market.  The  fit and machining is of a quality you'd expect from a German shop, and they shoot like a dream.  The bore is bright and shiny, and the trigger is smooth, both in double and single action.

This Makarov comes with a black soft-leather military holster, complete with the correct cleaning rod.  An extra clip is included, and the pistol is enclosed in a sturdy plastic, lockable carrying case.

I'm including an almost-full box of Winchester ammo.  Premium defense ammo is available, making the Makarov a desireable concealed-carry weapon.

The Makarov is to Russia what the 1911 is to us here in the U.S.   It became the Soviet Union's standard military side arm from 1951-1991, and remains in widespread use even after being replaced by a more modern 9mm Yarygin pistol.  The Makarov is still the service pistol of many Eastern European and former Soviet republics.  The East German Makarovs are clearly C&R eligible because the country of manufacture, the GDR, no longer exists.

I'm asking $350 for this East German Makarov, with the accessories and ammo.  It's perfect for home or car protection.  This would make a great Christmas gift for someone special.  Perfect East German Makarovs are hard to find, so contact me immediately before this one gets away.  You will not be disappointed.
